        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 15 at 10:29PM MDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 1029 PM MDT, a cluster of strong thunderstorms was located along
a line extending from 4 miles northeast of Marmarth to 8 miles
northwest of Mud Buttes to 19 miles northwest of Ladner. Movement
was east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Rhame, Marmarth, Mud Buttes, Griffin, Sunset Butte, and Pretty Butte.
</description>
        <instruction>These storms may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 400 AM MDT for
southwestern North Dakota.</instruction>
